items.title: Can domestic formulations shield Indian pharma from US pricing pressure in Q3?
items.description: Indian drugmakers anticipate a mixed third quarter. Domestic sales and new specialty drugs will drive growth. US generics will see new product boosts. Contract services and APIs are set for moderate gains. Sun Pharma and Lupin are poised for leadership. Cipla and Dr Reddy's face softer US sales. Divi's Laboratories expects strong custom synthesis growth.

items.title: Q3 results today: RIL, Wipro among 42 companies to report earnings on Friday
items.description: Apart from these, companies such as JSW Infrastructure, Poonawalla Fincorp, Central Bank of India, JB Chemicals, Tata Technologies, Sobha, KPI Green will also report their quarterly numbers

items.title: ICICI Bank Q3 preview: PAT growth seen up to 7.5% YoY, NII likely to rise 6–8%
items.description: ICICI Bank is set to announce its Q3FY26 results, with analysts projecting a steady performance. Profit After Tax (PAT) growth is anticipated between 1% and 7% year-on-year, supported by healthy loan growth in retail and SME segments. Net Interest Income (NII) is expected to rise 6-8% YoY, while Net Interest Margins (NIMs) are forecast to remain stable around 4.3%

items.title: Reliance Industries Q3 results today: What to expect and 5 key things to track
items.description: Reliance Industries is set to announce its Q3 results today, with analysts expecting a strong performance from its refining division, driven by higher diesel cracks and a weaker rupee. However, the retail segment faces headwinds from quick commerce losses and a consumption slowdown, while Jio's ARPU trajectory and petrochemical pain are key areas to watch.

items.title: HDFC Bank Q3 preview: PAT growth seen up to 13% YoY, NII likely to rise 4-8%. Here’s what investors can expect
items.description: HDFC Bank is set to announce its Q3 earnings on January 17th, with analysts projecting a year-on-year net profit growth of up to 13%. Net Interest Income is expected to rise between 4-8%. Investors will be closely watching management commentary on deposit mobilization and margin trajectory for future performance insights.

items.title: Tech Mahindra Q3 Results: Profit rises 14% YoY to Rs 1,122 crore, revenue up 8%
items.description: Tech Mahindra Q3 Results: Tech Mahindra reported a 14.1% year-on-year rise in December quarter consolidated profit to Rs 1,122 crore, with revenue climbing 8.3% to Rs 14,393 crore. The company saw a significant 47% year-on-year increase in new deal wins, reaching $1,096 million, highlighting strong momentum and sustained investments in AI-led offerings.

items.title: Wipro Q3 Results: Profit falls 7% YoY to Rs 3,119 crore; co declares dividend of Rs 6 per share
items.description: Wipro’s Q3 results showed mixed performance, with net profit down 7% YoY to Rs 3,119 crore even as revenue rose 6%. Margins improved to 17.6%, cash flows strengthened, and attrition fell, but deal bookings remained weak. The company guided for flat to 2% sequential IT services growth.

items.title: Federal Bank Q3 Results: Profit rises 9% YoY to Rs 1,041 crore
items.description: Federal Bank announced a significant rise in its third-quarter net profit, reaching Rs 1,041 crore. This marks an improvement from the previous year's earnings. The bank's total income also saw an increase. Asset quality metrics showed positive movement with a reduction in gross and net non-performing assets.

items.title: Central Bank of India Q3 Results: Profit jumps 32% YoY to Rs 1,263 crore as bad loans dip
items.description: Total income increased to Rs 10,969 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 9,739 crore in the same period of last year, Central Bank of India said in a regulatory filing.

items.title: Leela Palaces Hotels & Resorts Q3 Results: Consolidated net profit more than doubles to Rs 148 crore
items.description: Leela Palaces Hotels & Resorts announced a significant profit increase for the third quarter. Net profit rose to Rs 147.88 crore from Rs 56.40 crore a year ago. Revenue from operations also saw a strong jump. The company noted an impact from new Labour Codes. This performance highlights the brand's luxury positioning and pricing power.

items.title: Tech Mahindra Q3 results: Revenue & profit likely to jump on margin gains
items.description: Tech Mahindra is expected to report steady revenue growth and a sharp rise in profitability for the December quarter, driven by margin expansion and cost optimisation measures. According to estimates from six brokerages, revenue is projected to rise about 7% year-on-year, while profit after tax is likely to jump nearly 40%.

items.title: Wipro Q3 Results Press Conference Live: Margins, deal wins, Harman impact in focus
items.description: Wipro shares climbed ahead of its December-quarter earnings, with investors closely tracking margins, deal momentum, and the impact of recent acquisitions, including Harman. The IT major reports Q3FY26 results later today, followed by a management press conference. Street estimates suggest muted growth amid cautious global client spending. Brokerages expect low single-digit revenue growth, modest profit expansion, and near-term margin pressure from furloughs, deal ramp-ups, and integration costs related to Harman.

items.title: Tata Technologies Q3 Results: Profit slumps 96% YoY to Rs 7 crore
items.description: Tata Technologies Q3 Results: The company, which counts Jaguar Land Rover and Tata Motors among its largest clients, reported a 4% rise in revenue to Rs 1,366 crore during the quarter.

items.title: Reliance Industries Q3 Results: Profit rises marginally to Rs 18,645 crore; revenue up 11%
items.description: Reliance Industries Q3 Results: Mukesh Ambani-led Reliance Industries Ltd (RIL) on Friday posted a marginal 0.56% year-on-year (YoY) growth in its consolidated net profit at Rs 18,645 crore in the third quarter. Revenue from operations in the same period rose 11% YoY to Rs 2.69 lakh crore.

items.title: Federal Bank reports 9% rise in Q3 profit to Rs 1,041 crore on rising business income
items.description: Federal Bank announced a strong third quarter with net profit climbing 9% to Rs 1041 crore. This growth was driven by increased business and core income. Net interest income and operating profit reached record highs. The bank saw a reduction in bad loans. Advances grew 11% year-on-year. Deposits also increased by 12%.

items.title: Wipro Q3 Results: Net profit drops 7% YoY to ₹3,119 cr; dividend of ₹6 per share
items.description: IT services company Wipro on Friday reported a 7% year-on-year (YoY) decline in its consolidated net profit at Rs 3,119 crore in the third quarter. Revenue from operations in the same period increased 6% YoY to Rs 23,556 crore.The company's board approved an interim dividend of Rs 6 per share and fixed January 27 as the record date. The payment will be made on or before February 14.

items.title: Tech Mahindra Q3 Results: Profit jumps 14% YoY to Rs 1,122 cr, EBIT margin expands 290 bps to 13.1%
items.description: IT major Tech Mahindra on Friday reported that its December quarter consolidated profit after tax rose 14.1% year-on-year (YoY) to Rs 1,122 crore while revenue rose 8.3% YoY to Rs 14,393 crore.In USD terms, the revenue was 1.7% sequentially in constant currency terms while EBIT margin rose 100 basis points on a sequential basis to 13.1%.New deal wins TCV rose 47% YoY and 34.3% QoQ to $1,096 million, the company said in a regulatory filing.

items.title: Reliance Jio Q3 Results FY26: Profit jumps 11% YoY to Rs 7,629 crore; ARPU rises to Rs 213.7
items.description: Jio Q3 Results 2026:  Jio's average revenue per user (ARPU) increased to Rs 213.7 from Rs 211.4 sequentially.

items.title: Reliance Industries sees marginal profit growth in Q3 driven by O2C, Jio
items.description: Mukesh Ambani-led Reliance Industries Ltd (RIL) on Friday posted a marginal 0.56% year-on-year (YoY) growth in its consolidated net profit at Rs 18,645 crore in the third quarter. The profit is attributable to shareholders of the company. Revenue from operations in the same period rose 11% YoY to Rs 2.69 lakh crore. On a sequential basis, the profit increased 3% from Rs 18,165 crore reported in the September quarter. Revenues jumped 4% quarter-on-quarter.The oil-to-telecom conglomerate reported an EBITDA of Rs 50,932 crore, which is up 6% YoY, led by strong operating performance in Jio and O2C businesses.

items.title: Reliance Retail Q3 Results: Profit rises 3% YoY to Rs 3,551 crore; revenue up 9%
items.description: Reliance Retail Q3 Results: Reliance Retail reported a 2.7% YoY rise in Q3 profit to Rs 3,551 crore and 9.2% revenue growth. EBITDA increased 1.3% to Rs 6,915 crore, though margins softened. Store additions, strong festive demand across categories, rapid JioMart growth and steady fashion, lifestyle and electronics performance drove the quarter.
